 FC Sheriff Tiraspol Logo
Fotbal Club Sheriff, commonly known as Sheriff Tiraspol or simply Sheriff, is a Moldovan professional football club based in Tiraspol, a city located in the unrecognised breakaway state of Transnistria. Founded in 1997 as Tiras Tiraspol and rebranded the following year as Sheriff, it quickly established itself within Moldovan football. “The Wasps” recorded their debut in the first league in the 1998–99 season, when they also won their first trophy, the Moldovan Cup.
